Notes: bc there are two visit dates (and C1 table is merged first) this will show as VISITDATE_x
bc there are two visit dates (and registry table is merged second) this will show as VISITDATE_y

transformation: f"{int(row['BIRTHYR'])}-{int(row['BIRTHMO']):02d}-01" if pd.notna(row["BIRTHYR"]) and pd.notna(row["BIRTHMO"]) else None

LANG_MAP.get(int(row["LANGEASIEST"]), "Unknown") if pd.notna(row["LANGEASIEST"]) and LANG_MAP.get(int(row["LANGEASIEST"]), "Unknown") != "Other" else row["OTH1LANG"] if pd.notna(row["OTH1LANG"]) else None

LANGUAGE_PROFICIENCY_MAP.get(int(row["ENGPRS"]), "") if pd.notna(row["ENGPRS"]) and pd.notna(row["LANGEASIEST"]) and int(row["LANGEASIEST"]) == 1 else LANGUAGE_PROFICIENCY_MAP.get(int(row["SPANPRS"]), "") if pd.notna(row["SPANPRS"]) and pd.notna(row["LANGEASIEST"]) and int(row["LANGEASIEST"]) == 2 else LANGUAGE_PROFICIENCY_MAP.get(int(row["OTH1PRS"]), "") if pd.notna(row["OTH1PRS"]) and pd.notna(row["LANGEASIEST"]) and int(row["LANGEASIEST"]) == 3 else ""

row["LANGSPAN"] if pd.notna(row["LANGSPAN"]) and pd.notna(row["LANGEASIEST"]) and int(row["LANGEASIEST"]) == 1 else row["LANGENG"] if pd.notna(row["LANGENG"]) and pd.notna(row["LANGEASIEST"]) and (int(row["LANGEASIEST"]) == 2 or int(row["LANGEASIEST"]) == 3) else None

LANGUAGE_PROFICIENCY_MAP.get(int(row["SPANPRS"]), "") if pd.notna(row["SPANPRS"]) and pd.notna(row["LANGEASIEST"]) and pd.notna(row["LANGSPAN"]) and int(row["LANGEASIEST"]) == 1 else LANGUAGE_PROFICIENCY_MAP.get(int(row["ENGPRS"]), "") if pd.notna(row["ENGPRS"]) and pd.notna(row["LANGEASIEST"]) and (int(row["LANGEASIEST"]) == 2 or int(row["LANGEASIEST"]) == 3) else None

row["OTH1LANG"] if pd.notna(row["OTH1LANG"]) and pd.notna(row["LANGEASIEST"]) and (int(row["LANGEASIEST"]) == 1 or int(row["LANGEASIEST"]) == 2) else row["LANGSPAN"] if pd.notna(row["LANGSPAN"]) and pd.notna(row["LANGEASIEST"]) and int(row["LANGEASIEST"]) == 3 else None

LANGUAGE_PROFICIENCY_MAP.get(int(row["OTH1PRS"]), "") if pd.notna(row["OTH1PRS"]) and pd.notna(row["LANGEASIEST"]) and int(row["LANGEASIEST"]) != 3 else LANGUAGE_PROFICIENCY_MAP.get(int(row["SPANPRS"]), "") if pd.notna(row["SPANPRS"]) and pd.notna(row["LANGEASIEST"]) and pd.notna(row["LANGSPAN"]) and int(row["LANGEASIEST"]) == 3 else None

(int(row["MOCARECN"]) * 3 ) + (int(row["MOCARECC"]) * 2)  + int(row["MOCARECR"]) if pd.notna(row["MOCARECN"]) and pd.notna(row["MOCARECC"]) and pd.notna(row["MOCARECR"])  and row["MOCARECN"] != 88 and  row["MOCARECR"] != 88 else None
